= Swearing by Other than Allāh (Ḥalaf BiGhayr-Allāh


*Definition of Swearing (Ḥalaf):*

Linguistically: It means commitment or binding oneself to something.

In Islām: It is affirming a statement by mentioning something venerated, using one of the letters of oath which are -waaw (و), baa’ (ب), and taa’ (ت) lik saying: Wallāhi, Billāhi, Tallāhi (By Allāh).


*Other Names for Swearing:*

It is also referred to as:

- Al-Yamīn (the oath)
 
- Al-Qasam (the vow)


*The Legitimate Oath (Permissible Swearing):*


It must be:

 • By Allāh (e.g., Wallāhi, Billāhi, Tallāhi)
 
 • Or by one of His Names (e.g., By Ar-Rahmān, Al-‘Azīm, As-Samī‘)
 
 • Or by one of His Attributes (e.g., By Allāh’s Might, Mercy, Knowledge)
 

*Ruling on Swearing by Other than Allāh:*


There are two rulings:
 1. If a person swears by something and glorifies it to the level of worship, such as glorifying it like or more than Allāh, then this is Major Shirk (Shirk Akbar). This takes one out of the fold of Islām.
 

2. If a person venerates something (when swearing by it) but does not reach the level of equating it with Allāh’s veneration then this is Minor Shirk (Shirk Asghar).



*Evidence for the Ruling on Swearing by Other than Allāh:*


The Prophet #pbuh said:#quran-block[مَنْ حَلَفَ بِغَيْرِ اللَّهِ فَقَدْ كَفَرَ أَوْ أَشْرَكَ][“Whoever swears by other than Allāh has committed disbelief or shirk.”
(Reported by Ahmad, Abū Dāwūd, and At-Tirmidhī)@abuesa16[vol. 2, p.562 , \#1627]
]




*Examples of Swearing by Other than Allāh:*

 • Swearing by saints (awliyā’)
 
 • Swearing by the status of the Prophet #pbuh or status of saints
 
 • Swearing by someone’s life
 
 • Swearing by honour or trustworthiness
 


*Summary of the Rulings on Swearing:*


 • Swearing by anyone other than Allāh is prohibited and considered shirk.
 
 • Swearing falsely by Allāh is a major sin known as Yamīn Ghamūs (the immersing oath — because it plunges the one who swears into Hell).
 
 • Frequent swearing by Allāh even if truthful, without need is prohibited due to its disrespectful nature.
 
 • Swearing truthfully by Allāh when needed is permissible.
 


*Expiation (Kaffārah) for Swearing by Other than Allāh:*


The one who swears by other than Allāh should say: “Lā ilāha illa Allāh” (There is no deity worthy of worship except Allāh).
The evidence for this is the statement of the Prophet #pbuh:#hadith-block[مَنْ حَلَفَ فَقَالَ فِي حَلِفِهِ: وَاللَّاتِ وَالْعُزَّى، فَلْيَقُلْ: لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا اللَّهُ][“Whoever swears and says in his oath: ‘By al-Lāt and al-‘Uzzā,’ then let him say: ‘Lā ilāha illa Allāh.’”
(Agreed upon)@muslim[vol. 4, p.365 , \#1687]
]


